Package: stage
Title: Models for Estimating Stage-Transition Points
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Adam N. H.", "Smith", , "anhsmith@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The STAGE package implements Bayesian models for estimating 
    transition points between two classes. The flagship model is STAGE 
    (State Transition Analysis via Generative Estimator), which fits a 
    uniform plateau and a Gaussian tail to each class-conditional distribution. 
    The package provides functions for fitting single-population and 
    hierarchical multi-population models, extracting posterior transition 
    points (m50), producing predictions, and summarising uncertainty. 
    The methods are designed for applications such as length-at-maturity 
    estimation and other problems involving gradual class overlap.
